Description: Body sherd of Chian (?) fine-walled black-figured pottery small open vase; white slip; worn. Interior: large double-outlined rosette with alternate red and black petals; exterior: two friezes separated by a line; above, possible figure or animal at left break, incised rosette central, circumscribed rosette on right, with alternate red and black petals; below, sets of concentric circles with added dots.
Curator's comments: From same vase as 1924,1201.1153. Plausibly from a phiale, judging from the fine fabric.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.29)
